title: 784-D
statement: D. Touchy-Feely Palindromestime limit per test2 secondsmemory limit per test64 megabytesinputstandard inputoutputstandard outputInputThe only line of the input contains a string of digits. The length of the string is between1and10, inclusive.OutputOutput "Yes" or "No".ExamplesInput373OutputYesInput121OutputNoInput436OutputYes

processed.result:
Given a string of digits, determine if it reads the same backward as it does forward. If it does, output "Yes". Otherwise, output "No". 

For example:

* Input: 373  Output: Yes
* Input: 121  Output: Yes
* Input: 436  Output: No
Determine if a given string of digits reads the same backward as forward.
